WEBVTT

00:06.500 --> 00:11.275
♪

00:14.843 --> 00:18.275
[orchestra plays Lalo's "Cello Concerto"]

00:20.000 --> 00:26.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:47.172 --> 00:49.150
[dramatic accent notes]

00:49.200 --> 00:52.125
[cello solo continues]

00:52.175 --> 00:56.200
♪

00:56.250 --> 00:58.266
[dramatic notes]

01:24.950 --> 01:28.125
[end chords]

01:31.169 --> 01:34.300
Bravo! Bravo!

01:34.937 --> 01:37.890
[loud cheers and applause]

01:37.909 --> 01:40.028
Bellissimo! Bellissimo!

01:40.046 --> 01:43.281
I see you've been working
on your molto sul ponticello.

01:44.781 --> 01:48.015
And I see you've been
working on some cupcakes.

01:48.372 --> 01:52.103
[cheers and applause continues]

01:57.859 --> 02:01.168
[loud cheers and applause]

02:01.638 --> 02:03.971
Warren, may I say that your
playing is even more supple

02:03.971 --> 02:06.015
- than when I last saw you?
- Wow, thank you.

02:06.043 --> 02:08.181
I have been focusing a
lot on my bow technique.

02:08.205 --> 02:09.154
It shows.

02:09.274 --> 02:10.485
- And Dee Dee?
- Hmm?

02:10.533 --> 02:12.286
You're playing like a bearded tsunami.

02:12.304 --> 02:14.596
I do have a lot of unchecked rage.

02:14.638 --> 02:16.528
Bob, how is it you stay so fit?

02:16.552 --> 02:18.544
- You look great this season.
- 100 crunches a day.

02:18.664 --> 02:21.580
- That's how you do it.
- Adagio, Andrew, adagio.

02:21.940 --> 02:24.658
I don't want everybody feeling
too good about themselves.

02:24.706 --> 02:26.926
Ha ha. My apologies, Maestro. Gentlemen,

02:26.968 --> 02:28.738
I take back everything I just said,

02:29.008 --> 02:30.592
but may I tell you, sir,

02:30.946 --> 02:32.506
your performance tonight was magnificent.

02:32.542 --> 02:33.892
Oh, thank you, Andrew. Thank you.

02:33.910 --> 02:35.404
I'm so pleased that you're putting a nice,

02:35.428 --> 02:37.066
fresh coat of paint on this old vessel.

02:37.084 --> 02:38.110
Oh, you know how it is.

02:38.116 --> 02:39.616
- I do.
- I mean, when I said no

02:39.646 --> 02:40.810
- to Helsinki...
- Very painful...

02:40.840 --> 02:42.256
Great show, everybody.

02:43.150 --> 02:44.680
- Maestro...
- Michele, what...

02:44.746 --> 02:46.546
- Your favorite?
- What? No.

02:46.666 --> 02:48.400
I don't know what you're doing, Michele,

02:48.520 --> 02:49.858
I... I don't like cookies.

02:50.032 --> 02:51.478
They look delicious.

02:51.606 --> 02:52.780
May I?

02:53.122 --> 02:54.094
Please.

02:54.947 --> 02:57.340
I... I hope they didn't cool off too much.

02:57.397 --> 02:59.606
Mmm. Very good. You don't
know what you're missing.

02:59.726 --> 03:01.559
Maybe, yeah, but it's okay.

03:01.583 --> 03:04.007
I'll go do some after-show
"pilatos", you know?

03:04.050 --> 03:05.970
Just to ease the tension.

03:06.038 --> 03:07.382
Bye-bye, Andrew. Thank you very much.

03:07.406 --> 03:08.822
Ciao. Bye-bye.

03:09.230 --> 03:10.919
[whispers] What are pilatos?

03:11.082 --> 03:12.378
I don't know!

03:14.423 --> 03:15.735
- Hi.
- Hey, there.

03:16.259 --> 03:17.988
You're Hailey Rutledge, right?

03:18.446 --> 03:19.822
Uh, yeah.

03:19.872 --> 03:21.589
- I'm Andrew Walsh.
- I know.

03:21.613 --> 03:23.672
I actually have a bootleg of

03:23.792 --> 03:26.206
you playing the "Bach
Cello Suites" in Dresden.

03:26.590 --> 03:28.203
Oh, yes. I remember that concert

03:28.232 --> 03:30.545
and the East Germans
with their urtext fetish.

03:30.569 --> 03:31.787
Yeah. [Giggles]

03:31.807 --> 03:34.485
You think I could, uh...
hear that recording sometime?

03:34.605 --> 03:35.824
Um, yeah.

03:35.863 --> 03:37.941
I could probably find a
way to get it to you, so...

03:37.941 --> 03:38.858
- Hey.
- Hi.

03:38.877 --> 03:40.211
I bet you could.

03:40.702 --> 03:42.078
- Cyn.
- Andrew.

03:42.112 --> 03:44.008
How great to see you. You look smashing.

03:44.013 --> 03:44.949
Oh, my God. Look at you.

03:45.069 --> 03:47.148
Oh. [Sniffs] Mmm.

03:47.268 --> 03:49.766
How long's it been? Too long. Three years?

03:50.086 --> 03:52.540
Actually, I think I saw you last November.

03:52.852 --> 03:53.979
- Either way...
- [giggles]

03:53.979 --> 03:55.860
It's really great to, um...

03:56.455 --> 03:57.854
to play with you again. Finally.

03:57.883 --> 04:00.688
I was just introducing
myself to Hailey here.

04:00.758 --> 04:03.277
Turns out her picture's
on the poster outside.

04:03.311 --> 04:05.637
Seems she's the new face
of the New York Symphony.

04:05.675 --> 04:06.835
Oh, no.

04:06.858 --> 04:08.948
They just did that so they wouldn't
have to pay for stock photography.

04:08.979 --> 04:11.306
Great move on their
part, a pretty girl who...

04:11.336 --> 04:13.567
who loves Bach. These guys
know what they're doing.

04:13.577 --> 04:16.149
That PR department sexes up the, uh...

04:17.011 --> 04:18.048
entire operation.

04:18.095 --> 04:20.817
I'm not sure that's how they would put it.

04:20.863 --> 04:22.356
Now, this might be a little bit forward,

04:22.374 --> 04:24.370
but do either of you care to join me

04:24.420 --> 04:26.686
to see Lang Lang play tonight?

04:27.324 --> 04:28.829
Cyn, for old time's sake?

04:28.861 --> 04:29.670
I can't.

04:29.948 --> 04:31.616
Oh, okay.

04:31.644 --> 04:33.049
Hailey, for new time's sake?

04:33.059 --> 04:35.638
That sounds incredible, um... but...

04:35.651 --> 04:37.389
Look, I have this meet-and-greet

04:37.415 --> 04:40.781
with these desperate donors
down the hallway here.

04:40.961 --> 04:43.390
Shostakovich. [laughs]
It's a... funny word.

04:43.404 --> 04:45.109
But I only have 15 minutes, so

04:45.285 --> 04:46.375
if you want to join me,

04:46.542 --> 04:47.821
and you should...

04:49.106 --> 04:50.721
[singsong] it'll be fun.

04:54.148 --> 04:57.483
[humming]

05:02.093 --> 05:03.729
She looks good.

05:04.889 --> 05:06.234
We're born,

05:06.733 --> 05:08.605
we decide to be musicians,

05:09.016 --> 05:10.213
we grab an instrument.

05:10.226 --> 05:12.482
Then we grow up, and then we end up...

05:13.591 --> 05:15.005
- She looks really beautiful.
- She does.

05:15.037 --> 05:17.246
- Really beautiful, yeah.
- Really beautiful.

05:18.198 --> 05:20.116
I got some toilet paper for the house.

05:21.267 --> 05:23.106
Oh, that's great.

05:23.649 --> 05:24.995
Are you off to the donors' event?

05:25.050 --> 05:27.319
No, I've had four of
those already this week.

05:27.342 --> 05:29.227
I'm gonna go take in a late movie.

05:29.278 --> 05:30.522
- Good.
- Clear my head.

05:30.596 --> 05:31.538
- Yes.
- Mm-hmm.

05:31.789 --> 05:32.833
What about you?

05:33.407 --> 05:34.598
No. Me, I'm...

05:34.930 --> 05:36.764
I don't know. One of those days, you know?

05:36.812 --> 05:38.147
I'll see you at the house.

05:38.262 --> 05:39.801
Okay, good.

05:42.376 --> 05:44.977
Um, for the future,

05:46.312 --> 05:49.016
there's extra toilet paper under the sink.

05:49.367 --> 05:50.545
Okay.

05:54.226 --> 05:56.867
Now, there's a man who could use a ride.

05:56.886 --> 05:58.683
- Hey, Maestro.
- Come on, come on.

05:58.887 --> 06:00.981
- Well, you know...
- I promise

06:01.028 --> 06:02.778
I won't talk about my symphony.

06:02.826 --> 06:04.425
Scout's honor.

06:05.030 --> 06:06.112
Where do we put the bike?

06:06.227 --> 06:07.263
[thud]

06:11.292 --> 06:14.209
Two maestros in the backseat of a limo.

06:14.502 --> 06:17.379
Sounds like the beginning of an epic joke.

06:17.495 --> 06:19.778
[laughter]

06:20.716 --> 06:22.942
Thank you so much, Mrs. Blowenstruth.

06:22.990 --> 06:26.029
It is patrons like you
who give my music a home.

06:26.144 --> 06:27.448
- It's your dedication...
- Pardon my interruption,

06:27.453 --> 06:29.575
but this man has to get to
a photo shoot right away.

06:30.508 --> 06:31.650
Oh, Ms. Rutledge.

06:31.667 --> 06:34.195
I thought I told you never to interrupt me

06:34.200 --> 06:36.340
should I ever be with two
or more beautiful women.

06:36.341 --> 06:39.279
Yes, I understand, but it's
an emergency photo shoot, so...

06:39.325 --> 06:40.360
- Oh.
- Yes.

06:40.360 --> 06:41.794
- Emergency.
- Mm.

06:42.307 --> 06:44.621
I'm so sorry, Mrs. Blowenstruth.

06:44.736 --> 06:46.110
- Shall we?
- Of course.

06:46.127 --> 06:47.282
Take care.

06:48.301 --> 06:49.336
What's Lang Lang playing?

06:49.368 --> 06:51.683
Oh, I think you'll be
surprised by what he's playing.

06:52.360 --> 06:54.231
[overlapping chatter]

06:54.279 --> 06:55.764
- Whoo!
- Whoo!

06:56.513 --> 06:57.940
Hey, what's up? My friend.

06:58.014 --> 06:59.614
Hey, what's up, Andrew? My man.

06:59.649 --> 07:01.788
Hey. It's been a long,
long time, Lang Lang.

07:01.903 --> 07:02.995
How you doing?

07:03.018 --> 07:04.498
Doing good, good. How'd tonight go?

07:04.516 --> 07:06.143
- Everything good?
- Oh, excellent.

07:06.180 --> 07:08.079
How's my bud Rodrigo doing over there?

07:08.421 --> 07:10.131
- Oh, he's crushing it.
- Yeah?

07:10.151 --> 07:11.652
He's crushing it. He's
retooling the whole place.

07:11.660 --> 07:13.208
Hey, it's my pleasure to introduce

07:13.255 --> 07:15.071
the linchpin of the whole thing really,

07:15.089 --> 07:16.887
Hailey Rutledge, the brilliant oboist.

07:16.915 --> 07:18.869
- Pleasure meeting you.
- Likewise, yeah.

07:19.076 --> 07:21.037
It must be wild in the woodwind

07:21.069 --> 07:23.634
with Betty Cragdale being hurt, right?

07:23.653 --> 07:25.921
- Yes, it is...
- Hey, Manny.

07:25.951 --> 07:27.183
This level's too low.

07:28.047 --> 07:30.106
Andrew, how are you doing? Good to see you.

07:30.126 --> 07:32.334
- You look good.
- Hey, pleasure.

07:33.671 --> 07:35.823
Holy moly. Is that Emanuel Ax?

07:35.856 --> 07:36.895
You bet it is.

07:37.302 --> 07:38.601
I have a last point to finish.

07:38.619 --> 07:40.491
Yeah, go finish him off.

07:41.156 --> 07:42.732
- So good, right?
- Yeah.

07:43.854 --> 07:45.439
I feel I just died and went to heaven.

07:45.462 --> 07:46.733
[laughs]

07:48.845 --> 07:51.766
Oh, prosciutto and yogurt?

07:51.881 --> 07:55.829
Man cannot live by cured
meats and fermented milk alone.

07:56.027 --> 07:58.010
I'm fucking famished,

07:58.125 --> 08:00.044
and having received this...

08:00.069 --> 08:01.379
Here, take a look, Maestro.

08:01.771 --> 08:03.296
- I thought you didn't want...
- No, no, no.

08:03.310 --> 08:06.535
You misunderstand. This
is not my symphony, no.

08:06.896 --> 08:08.550
If this were a fugue,

08:08.777 --> 08:10.527
it would be a fugue of despair

08:10.642 --> 08:14.124
composed by my wife and
orchestrated by her lawyer.

08:14.138 --> 08:16.277
These are my divorce papers

08:16.392 --> 08:19.106
presented to me just this evening.

08:19.154 --> 08:20.460
Shit.

08:20.575 --> 08:22.604
A bittersweet symphony.

08:23.316 --> 08:24.404
The Verve.

08:24.665 --> 08:27.003
Touché, Maestro. Touché.

08:27.401 --> 08:28.423
You know what?

08:28.474 --> 08:30.859
Let's seize the fucking night.

08:30.872 --> 08:33.479
A new Tommy Pembridge for a new era.

08:33.594 --> 08:37.301
I mean, you know, I am of
course on the wagon, as you know.

08:37.325 --> 08:39.658
I think that we could just

08:39.773 --> 08:41.755
dangle our feet over the edge

08:41.811 --> 08:43.429
- and drag them right through the gravel.
- Give it to me.

08:43.488 --> 08:44.819
- What do you say?
- No, no, no.

08:44.934 --> 08:46.419
No, no, no. Give me the bottle.

08:46.446 --> 08:47.787
Would you look into my eyes?

08:48.165 --> 08:49.450
You don't need this, Maestro.

08:49.779 --> 08:51.539
This is poison, okay?

08:51.654 --> 08:52.930
This is poison for you.

08:53.247 --> 08:54.710
[whimpers]

08:54.758 --> 08:55.764
We don't need it.

08:55.879 --> 08:57.432
- Okay?
- Hmm. Mm.

08:57.547 --> 08:58.476
No. We don't need this.

08:58.591 --> 08:59.872
No, no.

09:00.250 --> 09:02.470
Jesus, man.

09:04.489 --> 09:06.089
Good save, Maestro.

09:06.204 --> 09:07.304
Good save.

09:07.970 --> 09:10.280
You are truly my hermano.

09:10.534 --> 09:12.263
Well, that's what hermanos are for.

09:12.932 --> 09:14.134
Of course.

09:16.360 --> 09:17.920
But if you want to dangle your feet,

09:18.446 --> 09:21.220
you want to seize the moment,

09:22.061 --> 09:23.942
we might as well learn to

09:24.270 --> 09:25.961
step on each other's hands.

09:27.570 --> 09:29.229
Forget our names.

09:29.571 --> 09:31.247
Look into the precipice.

09:32.468 --> 09:33.863
Look into the abyss.

09:35.638 --> 09:38.171
Come, come, come. I've got something.

09:39.488 --> 09:42.195
I got this from a friend
from Fort Lee, New Jersey.

09:42.237 --> 09:45.043
Oh! Jeez, smells like shit.

09:45.129 --> 09:46.040
I know.

09:46.088 --> 09:47.436
- I know.
- What is it?

09:47.459 --> 09:48.882
He told me it's resin

09:49.048 --> 09:51.632
with mushroom and some kind of frog venom.

09:51.641 --> 09:52.963
Can you smoke it?

09:53.078 --> 09:55.548
I think you have to do
it in a ritual, you know?

09:55.571 --> 09:57.594
Like, treat it with respect and...

09:58.052 --> 09:59.203
Mmm.

09:59.250 --> 10:00.727
Or we could just eat
it and see what happens.

10:00.778 --> 10:02.696
- Let's eat it. Mm-hmm.
- Yeah.

10:08.218 --> 10:10.951
[pop music plays]

10:11.136 --> 10:12.426
- Whoa!
- Fuck.

10:13.492 --> 10:14.907
[cheers and applause]

10:16.599 --> 10:18.563
You're definitely on an upward trajectory.

10:18.993 --> 10:21.891
- Bravo. Bravo.
- Thank you. Thank you.

10:22.555 --> 10:23.975
All right, where were we?

10:24.045 --> 10:26.678
Oh. So from a woman's point of view,

10:26.854 --> 10:28.645
should I call her or not?

10:28.693 --> 10:30.648
Do you believe that that's what she wants,

10:30.683 --> 10:32.154
or does it sound like
she was just saying...

10:32.194 --> 10:33.685
I don't know. That's why... [mutters].

10:34.266 --> 10:37.163
It's so complicated. I mean, I
would just go with your instinct.

10:37.181 --> 10:38.411
I mean, you're a great guy.

10:38.429 --> 10:40.806
She would be crazy not
to want to be with you.

10:40.921 --> 10:43.828
- Oh. Well.
- Yeah, I mean... I... whatever.

10:49.864 --> 10:51.374
[crowd whooping]

10:51.422 --> 10:52.859
Strike. Whoo!

10:53.362 --> 10:55.546
Uh-uh. Lang Lang.

10:55.848 --> 10:58.040
Joshua Bell, what are you doing here?

10:58.088 --> 10:59.809
Well, I'll tell you what I'm doing here.

10:59.814 --> 11:02.307
I'm noticing that you foot
faulted... see this line?

11:02.628 --> 11:04.686
You're not supposed to put
your foot over that line.

11:04.707 --> 11:06.380
Come on. This... it...

11:06.630 --> 11:08.906
Josh. Still Mr. Competitive.

11:08.963 --> 11:11.019
- Come on.
- Is that Josh Bell?

11:12.166 --> 11:13.936
I think he prefers Joshua.

11:13.984 --> 11:16.414
You put up with this
much, if at all, really...

11:16.453 --> 11:17.838
This much makes a big difference.

11:17.844 --> 11:19.396
- It happens.
- Yeah, I know, yeah,

11:19.423 --> 11:20.592
you don't have to do much...

11:20.597 --> 11:21.585
It's just like typing, right?

11:21.604 --> 11:24.326
With a violin, a
millimeter means, you know,

11:24.339 --> 11:26.184
the difference between an F and an F sharp,

11:26.216 --> 11:27.559
and conducting is like...

11:27.674 --> 11:29.802
if you're off by a millimeter,
what is that gonna do...

11:29.848 --> 11:31.534
- Come on.
- We're having a good time.

11:31.582 --> 11:33.093
Forget it. I just... just forget it.

11:33.141 --> 11:34.723
I don't want... ah, I'm just kidding.

11:34.771 --> 11:37.816
[dance music plays]

11:37.864 --> 11:39.063
♪

11:39.111 --> 11:40.621
Some people think

11:40.669 --> 11:43.594
that in order to play
the piano really well,

11:43.642 --> 11:46.615
what you need to do is
keep your fingers limber,

11:46.663 --> 11:48.437
but that's not true at all.

11:48.485 --> 11:49.636
It's the feet.

11:49.684 --> 11:51.794
Horovitz used to say,

11:51.842 --> 11:55.055
"If my feet don't walk,
my fingers don't run."

11:55.103 --> 11:57.764
And he was a pretty great pianist.

11:57.812 --> 12:01.432
Well, hasn't helped so far.

12:01.480 --> 12:04.597
I don't think it's working.

12:04.645 --> 12:06.851
I don't feel a thing.

12:06.899 --> 12:10.615
Maybe it's 'cause I have a tolerance to it

12:10.663 --> 12:15.027
through years of hard, hard living.

12:15.075 --> 12:20.709
Or maybe it's just my
good old English blood.

12:22.363 --> 12:24.018
You know... [grunts]

12:24.066 --> 12:28.261
my ancestors can be traced
back to the Battle of Hastings,

12:28.309 --> 12:30.036
1066.

12:30.084 --> 12:31.954
Take a... take a seat, Maestro.

12:32.002 --> 12:33.081
- Take a seat.
- Oh, thank you.

12:33.128 --> 12:34.064
There's a game I used to play

12:34.111 --> 12:35.094
when I was a kid.

12:35.142 --> 12:36.941
I give you a name,

12:36.989 --> 12:38.883
a theme, a something.

12:38.931 --> 12:40.058
- An image. An...
- Ooh!

12:40.105 --> 12:42.000
John Cage plays this game.

12:42.048 --> 12:43.630
Okay. Can we start?

12:43.678 --> 12:44.685
- Okay, yeah.
- Yeah.

12:44.733 --> 12:45.860
No baton. Eight seconds.

12:45.908 --> 12:48.137
No baton, because I don't need one.

12:48.185 --> 12:50.703
I can use my finger. Huh?

12:50.751 --> 12:52.022
- Good.
- You like that?

12:52.070 --> 12:53.892
- Yeah.
- Okay.

12:53.940 --> 12:55.786
[both humming]

12:55.834 --> 12:58.999
- Nightmares.
- I get along with them.

12:59.047 --> 13:00.245
- Good.
- I like them.

13:00.293 --> 13:01.684
- Good.
- They look into my eyes.

13:01.732 --> 13:02.835
- I look into their eyes.
- Good.

13:02.883 --> 13:03.986
They don't blink.

13:04.034 --> 13:05.496
Ten seconds. Exercise.

13:05.544 --> 13:06.743
Uh, no interest.

13:06.791 --> 13:08.589
Exercise? Walk.

13:08.637 --> 13:11.922
At what point did you become an adult?

13:11.970 --> 13:14.199
When I was born.

13:14.247 --> 13:15.302
[rhythmic humming]

13:15.350 --> 13:16.789
What about your father, though?

13:16.837 --> 13:18.059
Yeah, he's...

13:18.107 --> 13:20.361
he's competitive in the music.

13:20.409 --> 13:21.560
- You know?
- Yeah.

13:21.608 --> 13:23.982
He used to be a mambo conductor.

13:24.030 --> 13:25.516
- You know?
- Ah!

13:25.564 --> 13:26.643
Wonderful.

13:26.691 --> 13:28.777
[rhythmic scatting]

13:28.825 --> 13:30.671
I would like you to teach me

13:30.719 --> 13:32.709
some really filthy words in Spanish.

13:32.757 --> 13:34.867
- Yeah.
- Like "go fuck yourself"

13:34.915 --> 13:37.384
or "go fuck your mother"
or something like that.

